  "prompt": "What is the best HD led TV under 20000 rupees?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, finding the best HD LED TV under \u20b920,000 depends on your specific needs, such as screen size, brand preference, and features. Here are some top options that are highly rated and fit within this budget:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Mi 32-inch HD Ready LED TV**\n- **Price**: Around \u20b913,000\u2013\u20b916,000\n- **Key Features**: \n  - HD Ready (1366x768 resolution)\n  - PatchWall OS for smart features\n  - 20W speakers with Dolby Audio\n  - Multiple connectivity options (HDMI, USB, etc.)\n- **Why Buy**: Affordable, reliable, and packed with smart features for the price.\n\n---\n\n### **2. LG 32-inch HD Ready LED TV (32LM563BPTC)**\n- **Price**: Around \u20b916,000\u2013\u20b918,000\n- **Key Features**: \n  - HD Ready resolution\n  - LG\u2019s WebOS (lightweight smart TV platform)\n  - USB, HDMI, and USB connections\n  - Energy-efficient with low power consumption\n- **Why Buy**: Trusted brand with good picture quality and a user-friendly interface.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Samsung 32-inch HD Ready LED TV (32T4340AK)**\n- **Price**: Around \u20b915,000\u2013\u20b918,000\n- **Key Features**: \n  - HD Ready resolution\n  - Crystal Display technology for clear visuals\n  - USB and HDMI ports\n  - Slim design and decent sound quality\n- **Why Buy**: Known for durability and excellent color reproduction.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Thomson 32-inch HD Ready LED Smart TV (9PRO)**\n- **Price**: Around \u20b912,000\u2013\u20b914,000\n- **Key Features**: \n  - HD Ready resolution\n  - Android TV with Google Assistant and Chromecast\n  - 20W speakers\n  - Multiple connectivity options\n- **Why Buy**: Budget-friendly smart TV with Android TV features.\n\n---\n\n### **5. iFFALCON 32-inch HD Ready LED Smart TV (32H61)**\n- **Price**: Around \u20b913,000\u2013\u20b915,000\n- **Key Features**: \n  - HD Ready resolution\n  - Android TV with Google Play Store\n  - Dolby Audio and 20W speakers\n  - Multiple HDMI and USB ports\n- **Why Buy**: Great value for money with smart features and good sound quality.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Kodak 32-inch HD Ready LED TV (32HDX9000)**\n- **Price**: Around \u20b910,000\u2013\u20b912,000\n- **Key Features**: \n  - HD Ready resolution\n  - Basic connectivity (HDMI, USB)\n  - Affordable price\n- **Why Buy**: One of the most budget-friendly options for a decent HD TV.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Choosing the Best HD LED TV:**\n1. **Screen Size**: 32-inch is the most common size under \u20b920,000.\n2. **Resolution**: HD Ready (1366x768) is standard in this range; avoid full HD TVs as they may not fit the budget.\n3. **Smart Features**: If you want smart TV functionality, look for models with Android TV or other platforms.\n4. **Brand Reputation**: Stick to reliable brands like Mi, LG, Samsung, or Thomson.\n5. **Audio Quality**: Check for built-in speakers with decent wattage (20W or higher).\n6. **Connectivity**: Ensure there are enough HDMI and USB ports for your needs.\n\n---\n\nYou can compare these models on e-commerce platforms like Amazon, Flipkart, or Croma to find the best deals and ensure the TV meets your requirements.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
